1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

2
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:12,120
Hello, my favorite flashlight.

3
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:17,320
Hello, my favorite black bat.

4
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,760
Are you well?

5
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:23,280
No.

6
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:28,240
I miss my treasure.

7
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:34,360
Are you ready
for the happiest day of your life?

8
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:37,720
What are we doing?

9
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:43,119
We will do everything
that we've never done before.

10
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,280
Ready?

11
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:47,360
Yes, my treasure.

12
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:09,400
Darling.

13
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,720
{\an8}This place is beautiful.

14
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:16,399
{\an8}- Beautiful, right?
- Yes.

15
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,280
{\an8}It's as if we're in heaven.

16
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:25,440
Heaven's beauty is indescribable, darling.

17
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,360
It's our forever after.

18
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:32,400
Our home.

19
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:38,440
Promise we will meet there?

20
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:43,200
I'm happy here.

21
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:47,640
I'll stay here forever.

22
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:50,880
Forever, yes.

23
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:53,280
But not here.

24
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,600
In heaven.

25
00:02:57,880 --> 00:03:01,600
You must be strong.
You must fight to live on.

26
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:04,880
To live with my treasure.

27
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:08,120
I'm happy here as it is.

28
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:11,920
Right?

29
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:16,840
Darling, tell me.

30
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:19,280
Don't you like it?

31
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:24,880
Dear, I'm hungry.

32
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,360
Let's eat.

33
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:29,840
Anything for my treasure.

34
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:32,920
But this time, I'll cook.

35
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:34,960
Okay, my love.

36
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:40,759
Darling, we've been living together,

37
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:42,919
but this is our first time
cooking together.

38
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:43,880
Dear.

39
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:47,319
How's my cooking all this time?

40
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:48,720
Super delicious.

41
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:51,640
Really?

42
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:57,119
Is it really delicious or are you trying
not to hurt my feelings?

43
00:03:57,120 --> 00:04:00,759
They're delicious. Have I ever lied?

44
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:02,840
Okay, in that case,

45
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:04,880
taste this.

46
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,280
Is it salty?

47
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:17,958
No. It's okay.

48
00:04:17,959 --> 00:04:19,719
I would like some more.

49
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:21,200
- More? Okay.
- Yeah.

50
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:25,200
- Is it that good? Here.
- Darling, hold on!

51
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:43,960
Are you happy?

52
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:49,279
- Happiest day of your life?
- Absolutely.

53
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:50,520
Good.

54
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:56,080
Now, lie down.

55
00:04:58,120 --> 00:05:00,120
- Why?
- Go.

56
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,400
Okay.

57
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,480
Here?

58
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,319
Good night, dear.

59
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:16,680
Close your eyes and sleep.

60
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,880
You must return.

61
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,360
Wait.

62
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:42,400
Well...

63
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:47,040
I can't sleep and I won't sleep.

64
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:50,920
If I can only see you here,

65
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,759
then I will stay here forever.

66
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:58,559
You can't. This isn't your place.

67
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:00,879
Listen here.

68
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:05,519
The love between Husniya Radwa
and Thariq Ridzuwan is so strong.

69
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:09,839
So, nothing can stop me from being here.

70
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:11,320
You understand me now?

71
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:14,440
Okay, fine. You win.

72
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:17,159
- I know.
- It's true.

73
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:21,000
Husniya Radwa really loves
Thariq Ridzuwan.

74
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:27,400
So, we'll stay here together.
Forever. Okay?

75
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:30,520
I will be here for you.

76
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,280
Forever.

77
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:40,040
Wherever you go, I'll be there.

78
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,720
I promise.

79
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:34,079
<i>We have something to tell you.</i>

80
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:37,480
<i>Please brace yourself.</i>

81
00:08:38,760 --> 00:08:39,679
What is it?

82
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,400
Radwa...

83
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:48,720
She's gone.

84
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:53,800
Where did she go?

85
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:57,240
She's passed away.

86
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:02,920
Passed away?

87
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:11,200
Let's head to the hospital
and make arrangements for the deceased.

88
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,840
How did she die?

89
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:23,040
She suffered complications
during childbirth.

90
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,240
You mean...

91
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,560
Radwa was pregnant?

92
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,480
Radwa.

93
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:09,680
Forgive me, Radwa.

94
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:15,120
I didn't take care of you.

95
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:19,280
I didn't protect you.

96
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,640
I didn't...

97
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:26,160
I didn't even know you were pregnant.

98
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:28,600
Oh, God!

99
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:35,080
Oh, God!

100
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,080
What kind of father am I?

101
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:44,000
What kind of father am I?

102
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:57,800
Where are you going?

103
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,160
Out.

104
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:01,640
Where to?

105
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:06,039
To Radwa's funeral.

106
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:07,680
I won't allow it.

107
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:11,000
Since when does a husband
need a wife's permission?

108
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:14,839
She's our daughter.

109
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:15,839
What's wrong with you?

110
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:18,119
Don't ask me.

111
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:20,119
I've always wanted her to die.

112
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:23,279
God has granted my prayer.

113
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:24,840
She's dead now.

114
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:28,200
She's your flesh and blood!

115
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:30,479
You are heartless.

116
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:32,479
Don't berate me.

117
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:35,800
If you leave, we're over.

118
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:37,560
Do you dare?

119
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:44,200
She's mad.

120
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:09,480
Dato', is her family coming?

121
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:19,320
It's okay, Imam.

122
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:21,759
Let's just proceed.

123
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:23,000
Sure, Dato'.

124
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:35,440
Radwa.

125
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:45,240
I'm sorry, Ridz.

126
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:50,520
I couldn't wait for you to wake up

127
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:55,240
to bury Radwa.

128
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:33,319
{\an8}We will run a few tests soon.

129
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:34,920
{\an8}2 WEEKS LATER

130
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:37,759
What happened to Thariq, doctor?

131
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:40,599
Did we miss something?

132
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:43,119
Physically,

133
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:46,959
Mr. Thariq is almost fully recovered.

134
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:50,239
His bullet wound is healing.

135
00:13:50,240 --> 00:13:52,439
His breathing has stabilized.

136
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:55,480
His blood test showed positive signs.

137
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:58,319
He is healthy.

138
00:13:58,320 --> 00:14:01,320
Doctor, I have a question.

139
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:05,480
If he's healthy, why hasn't he woken up?

140
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:08,200
He should be.

141
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:10,840
But...

142
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:18,320
It seems like Mr. Thariq
has lost the will to live.

143
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:25,639
If there's nothing else,
I'll excuse myself.

144
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:27,240
- Okay, doctor.
- Yes.

145
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:49,080
- Wow, this place is huge!
- It's huge.

146
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:54,240
Darling, why is it that
when we were dating, got married,

147
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:56,439
and we were apart,

148
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:58,840
I didn't think about taking you here?

149
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:07,960
I'm sorry.

150
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:09,800
I'm sorry

151
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:13,560
I've been busy with work
and haven't had time for you.

152
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:17,120
It's your duty to do your job.

153
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:20,240
I'm very proud to be your wife.

154
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:28,599
That's all in the past.

155
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:32,320
I no longer have to think about work.
I want to spend all my time with you.

156
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:36,439
Wherever, whenever,

157
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,880
I'll be with you.

158
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:39,960
Would you like that?

159
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:44,880
Come. Let's go there.

160
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:46,360
Come.

161
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:51,199
{\an8}- Are you happy today?
- Happiest.

162
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,360
{\an8}Good.

163
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,320
Go to sleep.

164
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:55,959
No.

165
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:57,879
- Go to sleep.
- No.

166
00:15:57,880 --> 00:16:01,760
Do whatever you want. I will not sleep.

167
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:04,880
Why are you here?

168
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:06,440
Because...

169
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:09,000
Because of you.

170
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:12,120
Or is it out of guilt?

171
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:17,560
You promised to be with me
in the delivery room,

172
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:19,560
but you never came.

173
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:22,800
You were not there when I died.

174
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:27,760
So, which is it?

175
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:30,760
Are you here because of love

176
00:16:32,120 --> 00:16:33,600
or guilt?

177
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:46,240
<i>Mom,</i>

178
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:49,640
Radwa didn't leave anything for us?

179
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:55,520
That useless girl had nothing.

180
00:16:57,360 --> 00:16:59,520
Dad said she had a child.

181
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:05,318
Her husband is in a coma.
Nobody knows when he'll wake up.

182
00:17:05,319 --> 00:17:06,760
He could also die. Right?

183
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,999
Mom, let's take her child.

184
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:15,399
Hey! Over my dead body.

185
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:18,078
I don't want her descendants
to live in my house.

186
00:17:18,079 --> 00:17:22,119
Mom, think about it.

187
00:17:24,040 --> 00:17:25,318
It's done, right?

188
00:17:25,319 --> 00:17:27,358
Mom, we take her child

189
00:17:27,359 --> 00:17:29,840
and demand monthly child support
from the family.

190
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:33,640
We could get at least
5,000 ringgit a month.

191
00:17:36,040 --> 00:17:38,199
You're dumb.

192
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,400
Do you think
they would simply give you money?

193
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:45,439
Just say that before Radwa gave birth,

194
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:50,639
she came to our house
and sought your forgiveness.

195
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:52,799
She asked for blessings.

196
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:55,079
And she professed her wishes.

197
00:17:55,080 --> 00:17:58,639
She said that if something happened
to her and her husband,

198
00:17:58,640 --> 00:18:00,880
she wanted you to care for her child.

199
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:04,199
Do you think they would fall for that?

200
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,519
Who will take care of the child? You?

201
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:09,240
You can't even take care
of your own child.

202
00:18:09,840 --> 00:18:12,400
Don't dream of taking care
of someone else's child.

203
00:18:13,520 --> 00:18:15,199
Mom!

204
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:17,199
We don't need to take care of the child.

205
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:20,759
We'll hire a sitter
using her in-laws' money.

206
00:18:20,760 --> 00:18:23,640
This is easy money!

207
00:18:26,840 --> 00:18:28,280
That's a better idea.

208
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:30,600
I told you.

209
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:34,280
I can't wait.

210
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:40,040
Ridz.

211
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:43,400
I've never blamed anyone

212
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:46,080
or myself,

213
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:51,640
but whatever happened was fate.

214
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:57,760
If I hadn't come to see you that day,

215
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,760
none of this would've happened.

216
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:07,120
When you are ready, wake up.

217
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,760
I love Thalia, Ridz.

218
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:18,960
But I know

219
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:23,960
it's incomparable to your love for Radwa.

220
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:27,160
I don't like to blame others, Ridz,

221
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:29,600
but in this case,

222
00:19:32,080 --> 00:19:33,120
it's my fault.

223
00:19:34,880 --> 00:19:37,080
All this happened

224
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:41,000
because of me.

225
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:45,720
<i>If lying here, sleeping like this,</i>

226
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:51,200
could ease your pain of losing Radwa,

227
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:55,200
don't wake up yet.

228
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:01,960
Take as much time as you need.

229
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:06,079
Ridz, it hurts.

230
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:08,600
I can't bear all this.

231
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:11,440
Wake up, Ridz.

232
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:17,320
You're the Holy Dragon's strength.

233
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:20,280
We understand.

234
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:26,160
We would do the same
for the people we love.

235
00:20:31,280 --> 00:20:33,000
When I was captured

236
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:36,200
and tortured,

237
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:40,920
it was the first time
I came close to death.

238
00:20:42,160 --> 00:20:44,040
I was afraid at that time.

239
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:49,680
But not of death.

240
00:20:52,240 --> 00:20:55,320
I was afraid to leave my family.

241
00:20:57,400 --> 00:21:01,080
Leaving Rania and Adriana.

242
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:05,720
I swear I couldn't, Ridz.

243
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:10,240
What would happen to them
if I weren't around?

244
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:16,000
What if they miss me?

245
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:21,560
Who would put my child to bed?

246
00:21:25,080 --> 00:21:28,400
Who would finish off
Rania's salty chili fried rice?

247
00:21:35,240 --> 00:21:37,480
Even if it was fate,

248
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:44,240
that fear would still haunt me.

249
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:47,320
But the feeling quickly faded

250
00:21:47,880 --> 00:21:50,200
when I was reminded of you, Ridz.

251
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:53,320
I suddenly felt strong

252
00:21:57,120 --> 00:22:00,600
because I was sure
you would come save me, Ridz.

253
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:05,800
And I would not die

254
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:11,200
because you were around.

255
00:22:13,560 --> 00:22:16,400
And you really came to save me.

256
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:19,400
Because of you,

257
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:24,960
I still get to see my family, Ridz.

258
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:31,520
But because of me,

259
00:22:33,320 --> 00:22:37,040
you couldn't be with Radwa
when she needed you.

260
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:42,240
Wake up, Ridz.

261
00:22:43,880 --> 00:22:45,880
I want to apologize to you.

262
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:53,120
I miss you, Ridz.

263
00:22:56,680 --> 00:22:57,920
<i>Wake up, Ridz.</i>

264
00:23:02,480 --> 00:23:05,200
<i>You promised to be with me
in the delivery room,</i>

265
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:07,840
<i>but you never came.</i>

266
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:11,080
<i>You were not there when I died.</i>

267
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:18,120
<i>So, which is it?</i>

268
00:23:19,080 --> 00:23:20,880
<i>Are you here because of love</i>

269
00:23:22,720 --> 00:23:24,000
<i>or guilt?</i>

270
00:23:39,720 --> 00:23:44,680
- I love you, Radwa, but--
- Please don't feel guilty.

271
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:51,360
I died because it was my time to die.

272
00:23:52,120 --> 00:23:54,239
Even if you were around,
you couldn't have done anything.

273
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:56,480
But at least I'd be by your side.

274
00:24:00,320 --> 00:24:02,600
I was always by your side.

275
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:06,400
When you really needed me, I wasn't there.

276
00:24:11,480 --> 00:24:12,999
It's all my fault.

277
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:14,280
No, dear.

278
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:16,439
It's not your fault.

279
00:24:16,440 --> 00:24:18,240
I'm at fault.

280
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:22,240
I was arrogant.

281
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:26,680
I was smug with God.

282
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:31,520
That night,

283
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:37,720
I was so confident
I could save Adrean and Haider.

284
00:24:39,560 --> 00:24:41,240
And then go back

285
00:24:43,280 --> 00:24:44,800
to be with you during delivery.

286
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:49,600
I was so cocky.

287
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:53,960
I forgot to seek God's protection.

288
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:58,760
I didn't even say my prayer.

289
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:02,880
I thought I could complete
the mission alone.

290
00:25:07,280 --> 00:25:09,680
But when I really needed God,

291
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:16,040
I had forsaken Him.

292
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:20,520
I was shot.

293
00:25:21,320 --> 00:25:24,439
I drowned and nearly died.

294
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:25,560
But instead,

295
00:25:28,520 --> 00:25:29,920
you died.

296
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:35,920
This is all my fault.
I was arrogant with God.

297
00:25:40,120 --> 00:25:42,160
You think I died

298
00:25:43,160 --> 00:25:45,200
as a punishment from God?

299
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:51,520
You died because of me.

300
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:54,960
No.

301
00:26:03,600 --> 00:26:04,720
But it's all in the past.

302
00:26:06,760 --> 00:26:08,280
I don't want to be sad anymore.

303
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:12,160
This is our happy place

304
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:15,800
and will forever be our happy place.

305
00:26:25,760 --> 00:26:27,960
It's nice having a movie night like this.

306
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:31,640
All we did was argue back then.

307
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:43,120
I love you.

308
00:26:50,760 --> 00:26:51,879
I love you...

309
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:53,600
more.

310
00:26:58,680 --> 00:27:00,600
Mira Filzah looks like you.

311
00:27:01,480 --> 00:27:03,360
But of course you're prettier.

312
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:08,200
Of course, we are beauties.

313
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:11,880
But short.

314
00:27:22,520 --> 00:27:23,400
What?

315
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:34,160
The lizard wants us to watch the TV.

316
00:27:41,280 --> 00:27:42,120
<i>Gosh.</i>

317
00:27:43,480 --> 00:27:46,040
How do we assemble this thing?
It's such a hassle.

318
00:27:46,680 --> 00:27:50,600
Mom, read the instructions
before starting.

319
00:27:52,800 --> 00:27:55,719
What a headache. Call your dad.

320
00:27:55,720 --> 00:27:58,079
- Let him do it.
- No, Mom.

321
00:27:58,080 --> 00:28:01,240
If he knows, he might ruin our plan.

322
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:04,160
He doesn't dare to go against me.

323
00:28:07,600 --> 00:28:09,880
- Call him.
- Dad!

324
00:28:11,280 --> 00:28:12,879
Where's that old man?

325
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:14,400
Dad!

326
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:20,039
This.

327
00:28:20,040 --> 00:28:22,959
Put this together. I don't know how to.

328
00:28:22,960 --> 00:28:25,560
Why is there a baby crib?

329
00:28:26,760 --> 00:28:30,239
I want to take in Radwa's child.

330
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:33,479
Are you mad? I won't allow it!

331
00:28:33,480 --> 00:28:35,320
How dare you call me mad?

332
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:37,800
You dare go against me now.

333
00:28:38,600 --> 00:28:41,119
Are you not done torturing Radwa?

334
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:43,600
Now, you want to abuse her child?

335
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:45,759
What?

336
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:48,839
You want to threaten me with divorce?

337
00:28:48,840 --> 00:28:50,839
Do you think I'm scared?

338
00:28:50,840 --> 00:28:52,599
I can make it happen anytime.

339
00:28:52,600 --> 00:28:57,639
If you want a divorce,
I can make it happen! Get it?

340
00:28:57,640 --> 00:29:01,040
- Don't be rude, Dad.
- Don't be rude to me!

341
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:04,000
Insolent child.

342
00:29:04,840 --> 00:29:07,119
Hey, I want to know.

343
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:10,080
Don't you want to take care
of your grandchild?

344
00:29:10,680 --> 00:29:13,919
Don't you want to care for Radwa's child?

345
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:16,839
Tell me. Where's her child?

346
00:29:16,840 --> 00:29:20,160
At Radwa's house or Thariq's mom's house?

347
00:29:23,920 --> 00:29:24,760
Hey!

348
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:43,640
How's the baby?

349
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:48,079
Getting better. The jaundice has subsided.

350
00:29:48,080 --> 00:29:49,440
But she refuses milk.

351
00:29:57,680 --> 00:29:59,880
How's Ridz, darling?

352
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:01,320
Ridz...

353
00:30:02,520 --> 00:30:04,720
He's the same.

354
00:30:06,080 --> 00:30:07,759
Poor Tia.

355
00:30:07,760 --> 00:30:11,280
She lost her mom and Ridz is unconscious.

356
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:26,360
Death can make us question fate.

357
00:30:27,800 --> 00:30:31,840
I have 1,0001 reasons to love you.

358
00:30:32,680 --> 00:30:34,799
You know what the first one is?

359
00:30:34,800 --> 00:30:38,240
You always put God first.

360
00:30:39,160 --> 00:30:42,360
Whatever you do, you do it for God.

361
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:45,440
You love me for God too. Correct?

362
00:30:47,040 --> 00:30:48,080
Yes.

363
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:53,199
But if your love for me
distorts your judgment of God,

364
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:54,399
stop it.

365
00:30:54,400 --> 00:30:56,680
Stop loving me!

366
00:30:58,680 --> 00:31:03,040
I don't want to be a wife who ruins
her husband's relationship with God!

367
00:31:10,280 --> 00:31:13,039
Why are you mad? Don't be sad.

368
00:31:13,040 --> 00:31:16,040
- I told you this is our--
- Stop it!

369
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:18,440
Enough! Wake up!

370
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:35,079
That was her last wish to me.

371
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:36,480
I hope...

372
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:43,999
Dato' and Datin could help

373
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:46,880
fulfill her wish.

374
00:31:53,440 --> 00:31:54,800
Look, ma'am.

375
00:31:55,800 --> 00:31:57,880
If that was her final wish,

376
00:31:58,480 --> 00:32:00,600
then it's a responsibility
she's entrusted to you.

377
00:32:01,640 --> 00:32:04,120
We will fulfill it.

378
00:32:04,720 --> 00:32:05,560
Dear.

379
00:32:06,360 --> 00:32:09,680
Thank you, Dato'! Thank you, Datin!

380
00:32:10,560 --> 00:32:12,199
You see...

381
00:32:12,200 --> 00:32:15,679
She's also my first grandchild.

382
00:32:15,680 --> 00:32:19,760
I really wish to care for her.

383
00:32:21,760 --> 00:32:24,800
What should we call her?

384
00:32:25,520 --> 00:32:27,359
Call her?

385
00:32:27,360 --> 00:32:29,880
What do you mean?

386
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:35,519
For instance, we call our son,
Thariq Ridzuwan, "Ridz."

387
00:32:35,520 --> 00:32:39,039
What about our granddaughter?

388
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:41,640
- What's the name?
- What's her name?

389
00:32:42,400 --> 00:32:44,680
My goodness.

390
00:32:45,520 --> 00:32:48,360
You don't know
your first grandchild's name?

391
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:51,880
Look.

392
00:32:52,480 --> 00:32:54,440
Give us some time

393
00:32:55,120 --> 00:32:57,479
because Tia is still in the hospital.

394
00:32:57,480 --> 00:32:59,160
The hospital?

395
00:32:59,920 --> 00:33:02,559
Is she ill?

396
00:33:02,560 --> 00:33:06,080
Jaundice. Don't you know?

397
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:09,119
You can take care of her first.

398
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:11,640
Once she's healthy, send her to us.

399
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:21,920
Please have a drink.

400
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:27,639
Why are you eager to get rid of me?

401
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:29,280
Don't you love me?

402
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:32,719
- Honey, don't be like this.
- Don't you care about me?

403
00:33:32,720 --> 00:33:35,400
I'll be heartbroken
having lost you forever.

404
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:39,360
Let me stay here! Why not?

405
00:33:40,080 --> 00:33:42,079
There's no problem here!
No mission, no work.

406
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:43,880
No Farez, no Aina. Nothing!

407
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:45,600
Just the two of us!

408
00:33:47,720 --> 00:33:49,520
You don't love me, do you?

409
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:51,599
Honey.

410
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:54,960
Do you hate me so much
that you're eager to be rid of me?

411
00:34:02,360 --> 00:34:03,800
Why are you so mean?

412
00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:09,239
Can't you love me
the way I love you, Radwa?

413
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:13,520
I...

414
00:34:14,600 --> 00:34:16,760
regret marrying you.

415
00:34:21,159 --> 00:34:22,920
I regret loving you.

416
00:34:24,679 --> 00:34:26,360
I regret knowing you.

417
00:34:29,400 --> 00:34:30,800
You want to get rid of me?

418
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:35,080
You want to get rid of me?

419
00:34:37,880 --> 00:34:38,719
Fine.

420
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:41,920
I'll leave.

421
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:47,760
You will never see me again.

422
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:51,880
I...

423
00:34:53,600 --> 00:34:54,840
hate you.

424
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:59,120
I honestly hate you, Husniya Radwa.

425
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:28,719
Darling.

426
00:35:28,720 --> 00:35:30,759
Tia can't stop crying.

427
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:33,679
She's been crying for a long time.

428
00:35:33,680 --> 00:35:37,399
The doctor is giving her a blood test.

429
00:35:37,400 --> 00:35:39,640
Calm down.

430
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:41,800
Take a deep breath.

431
00:35:43,720 --> 00:35:45,679
Now tell me what happened.

432
00:35:45,680 --> 00:35:50,159
This morning, the doctor came by
and said she was okay

433
00:35:50,160 --> 00:35:51,239
and could go home.

434
00:35:51,240 --> 00:35:53,519
I was excited and called Mom.

435
00:35:53,520 --> 00:35:55,679
But she said not to.

436
00:35:55,680 --> 00:35:57,959
I have to send her to Radwa's mom.

437
00:35:57,960 --> 00:36:00,479
They will take care of Tia.

438
00:36:00,480 --> 00:36:03,279
Why? That can't be.

439
00:36:03,280 --> 00:36:04,679
That's the issue.

440
00:36:04,680 --> 00:36:08,519
They said that if something happened
to Radwa and Ridz,

441
00:36:08,520 --> 00:36:11,239
Radwa's last wish was
for them to care for Tia.

442
00:36:11,240 --> 00:36:14,559
Ridz wouldn't allow it.
Do they have proof?

443
00:36:14,560 --> 00:36:19,999
No. But Dad said we have nothing
to prove otherwise.

444
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:25,320
So, if we refuse to fulfill Radwa's wish,
we're wrong.

445
00:36:26,640 --> 00:36:29,880
Okay, I understand.

446
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:33,080
But why can't Tia stop crying?

447
00:36:34,160 --> 00:36:35,399
I don't know.

448
00:36:35,400 --> 00:36:39,959
After speaking with Mom,
I talked to Tia as usual.

449
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:44,519
I told her she's healthy and can go home,
but she can't leave yet.

450
00:36:44,520 --> 00:36:48,519
Then we have to send her
to her evil grandma's house.

451
00:36:48,520 --> 00:36:52,959
After I said that,
she's been crying nonstop.

452
00:36:52,960 --> 00:36:55,919
I pity her.
She's been crying for quite a while.

453
00:36:55,920 --> 00:36:58,200
What should we do?

454
00:37:01,600 --> 00:37:04,080
This is not real, dear.

455
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:09,720
I am not real.

456
00:37:10,640 --> 00:37:14,840
The real Radwa will tell you
that she loves you very much.

457
00:37:16,160 --> 00:37:20,400
That she was happiest
when she was with you.

458
00:37:22,200 --> 00:37:25,640
You're the best gift for her.

459
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:31,280
And she's proud to have given you a child.

460
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:36,360
This is not real, dear.

461
00:37:37,920 --> 00:37:43,440
In reality, you would never yell at Radwa.

462
00:37:44,160 --> 00:37:50,160
You would never think badly of me
and say those things to me.

463
00:37:51,640 --> 00:37:53,800
Because you are a nice person.

464
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:58,600
That's why you can't be here.

465
00:38:02,200 --> 00:38:04,440
I can't bear to lose you.

466
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:11,360
I can't live without you.

467
00:38:14,720 --> 00:38:15,560
I...

468
00:38:17,240 --> 00:38:18,880
I don't have the strength.

469
00:38:22,960 --> 00:38:25,480
I'm not strong without you.

470
00:38:28,720 --> 00:38:31,320
I'll always be with you.

471
00:38:32,960 --> 00:38:34,200
In here.

472
00:38:37,080 --> 00:38:40,080
For as long as you need.

473
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:45,320
You are strong.

474
00:38:47,520 --> 00:38:49,560
You're my Thariq Ridzuwan.

475
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:05,879
{\an8}Do we still have money for shopping?

476
00:39:05,880 --> 00:39:08,599
{\an8}Look, we spent thousands.

477
00:39:08,600 --> 00:39:10,839
{\an8}Of course we do.

478
00:39:10,840 --> 00:39:13,600
{\an8}Just use the credit card.

479
00:39:14,200 --> 00:39:17,519
Just claim the expenses from Ridz's dad.

480
00:39:17,520 --> 00:39:21,239
If he asks what we spent so much on,

481
00:39:21,240 --> 00:39:25,279
just say we bought baby stuff.

482
00:39:25,280 --> 00:39:29,600
Create more soppy tales for them.

483
00:39:31,080 --> 00:39:36,279
Say, "Uncle, Dad is retired."

484
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:40,879
"Mom is a housewife and has never worked."

485
00:39:40,880 --> 00:39:46,200
"Radwa left us with no money.
We're penniless."

486
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:49,199
Who knows, after hearing that,

487
00:39:49,200 --> 00:39:54,119
he'd give us 20,000 to 30,000 a month.

488
00:39:54,120 --> 00:39:56,040
It would be worth it.

489
00:39:59,320 --> 00:40:02,000
Radwa's child. Hey.

490
00:40:03,920 --> 00:40:06,519
- Come with me.
- Where to?

491
00:40:06,520 --> 00:40:08,559
Let's go to the hospital

492
00:40:08,560 --> 00:40:12,439
and visit Radwa's child to see
if she's really sick and in the ward.

493
00:40:12,440 --> 00:40:15,880
If that's the case, once she's healthy,

494
00:40:16,640 --> 00:40:19,640
we'll take her under our care.

495
00:40:20,800 --> 00:40:22,880
- You're right.
- Let's go.

496
00:40:32,800 --> 00:40:34,080
Tia.

497
00:40:36,040 --> 00:40:37,120
Tia.

498
00:40:46,040 --> 00:40:47,640
Baby Tia misses her dad.

499
00:41:00,960 --> 00:41:02,480
My baby.

500
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:05,200
Darling.

501
00:41:06,240 --> 00:41:09,879
I would do anything

502
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:13,960
to hug and kiss Baby Tia.

503
00:41:14,920 --> 00:41:16,520
But I can't.

504
00:41:20,680 --> 00:41:22,000
It's okay

505
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:25,200
because you're around.

506
00:41:26,600 --> 00:41:28,560
You can comfort me

507
00:41:29,160 --> 00:41:31,040
when I miss my child.

508
00:41:31,640 --> 00:41:34,080
But you must comfort me all the time

509
00:41:34,760 --> 00:41:37,999
because I will always think of her
and worry about her.

510
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:40,600
Because she's alone there.

511
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:45,639
She has no father or mother
to put her to sleep,

512
00:41:45,640 --> 00:41:50,040
feed, hug, and kiss her.

513
00:41:52,040 --> 00:41:53,799
When she's grown,

514
00:41:53,800 --> 00:41:57,680
other kids would have their parents
to send them to school.

515
00:41:58,640 --> 00:42:03,080
Other kids would have parents
to celebrate their birthdays.

516
00:42:04,240 --> 00:42:05,520
But not her.

517
00:42:06,560 --> 00:42:11,000
Other kids would have parents
to say "I love you" to them.

518
00:42:13,040 --> 00:42:18,199
Radwa would do anything
to hug, kiss, and smell her

519
00:42:18,200 --> 00:42:20,400
for one last time!

520
00:42:21,320 --> 00:42:23,160
But I can't!

521
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:28,240
You could! Only you could do that!

522
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:50,360
Thalia.

523
00:42:51,640 --> 00:42:52,560
Mom.

524
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:57,920
Come, Tia.

525
00:43:09,520 --> 00:43:10,799
My goodness!

526
00:43:10,800 --> 00:43:12,600
Gosh.

527
00:43:13,360 --> 00:43:15,280
My grandchild is so cute!

528
00:43:15,880 --> 00:43:16,960
What do you want?

529
00:43:17,840 --> 00:43:19,639
I just wanted to say

530
00:43:19,640 --> 00:43:22,320
that my granddaughter is cute.

531
00:43:23,040 --> 00:43:26,920
Okay, look, Dato', Datin.

532
00:43:27,800 --> 00:43:34,039
Since our granddaughter is healthy
and can be discharged,

533
00:43:34,040 --> 00:43:37,119
as we've agreed,

534
00:43:37,120 --> 00:43:39,960
I will take her home and care for her.

535
00:43:40,920 --> 00:43:41,800
No!

536
00:43:42,720 --> 00:43:43,999
Why not?

537
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:46,519
Her dad is here. He'll take care of her.

538
00:43:46,520 --> 00:43:50,399
Look at Ridz. He's in a coma.

539
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:53,600
How can he take care of the baby?

540
00:44:01,120 --> 00:44:03,360
For all the pain you've been through,

541
00:44:05,520 --> 00:44:06,680
I'm sorry.

542
00:44:08,720 --> 00:44:11,720
For all the pain you're going through,

543
00:44:13,760 --> 00:44:15,080
I forgive you.

544
00:44:31,840 --> 00:44:33,560
I love you, Thariq Ridzuwan.

545
00:44:36,480 --> 00:44:37,520
Good night.

546
00:44:41,800 --> 00:44:43,720
Now, wake up, dear.

547
00:44:50,920 --> 00:44:54,960
Ridz can take care of her.
What's the problem?

548
00:44:56,960 --> 00:45:00,519
Her dad is in a coma.
He's as good as dead.

549
00:45:00,520 --> 00:45:01,879
Rude!

550
00:45:01,880 --> 00:45:03,119
Mom!

551
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:07,599
Don't you touch my daughter!

552
00:45:07,600 --> 00:45:09,639
Your daughter was rude.

553
00:45:09,640 --> 00:45:11,320
You should advise her.

554
00:45:11,920 --> 00:45:15,159
Rude! Hey, she's not your child!

555
00:45:15,160 --> 00:45:16,999
She's my brother's daughter!

556
00:45:17,000 --> 00:45:18,720
She's my sister's daughter!

557
00:45:19,560 --> 00:45:21,160
She's my child.

558
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:25,400
Thank God.

559
00:45:36,960 --> 00:45:39,200
Tia Radia binti Thariq Ridzuwan.

560
00:45:41,840 --> 00:45:42,879
{\an8}My precious.

561
00:45:42,880 --> 00:45:45,600
{\an8}TO BE CONTINUED

562
00:45:54,440 --> 00:45:58,719
{\an8}I will kill Thariq Ridzuwan.

563
00:45:58,720 --> 00:46:00,760
{\an8}I promised Radwa

564
00:46:01,640 --> 00:46:06,759
{\an8}that I'll take care of Tia a thousand
times better than I ever took care of her.

565
00:46:06,760 --> 00:46:07,999
{\an8}Aina! Tia!

566
00:46:08,000 --> 00:46:10,080
{\an8}Aina took Tia away, Ridz!

567
00:46:11,120 --> 00:46:13,199
{\an8}I'm Farez, your husband.

568
